quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  73,1,"O you the (sleeping) enwrapped one!"{1},footnotes:1:1
  73,2,"Stand up in Prayer by night, all but a small part of it;"{1},footnotes:1:1
  73,3,"half of it, or reduce it a little;"
  73,4,"or add to it a little; and recite the Qur'an slowly and distinctly."{1}{2},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2
  73,5,"Behold, We shall cast upon you a Weighty Word."{1},footnotes:1:1
  73,6,"Surely getting up at night is the best means of subduing the self and is more suitable for uprightness in speech."{1}{2}{3},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2,footnotes:3:3
  73,7,"You are indeed much occupied during the day with the affairs of the world."
  73,8,"So remember the name of your Lord and devote yourself to Him with exclusive devotion."{1},footnotes:1:1
  73,9,"He is the Lord of the East and the West; there is no god but He. So take Him alone for your Guardian,"{1},footnotes:1:1
  73,10,"And bear patiently the vain things they utter, and gracefully forsake them."{1},footnotes:1:1